%N A396855 Number of partitions of n into two parts with disjoint decimal digit sets.
%H A396855 Michael S. Branicky, <a href="/A396855/b396855.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%e A396855 a(23) = 8 since the valid pairs are (1,22), (3,20), (4,19), (5,18), (6,17), (7,16), (8,15), (9,14).
%o A396855 (Python)
%o A396855 def a(n): return sum(1 for i in range(1, (n-1)//2+1) if not set(str(i)) & set(str(n-i)))
%o A396855 print([a(n) for n in range(76)])
%o A396855 (PARI) a(n) = sum (x=1, n, (x<n-x) && (#setintersect(Set(digits((x))), Set(digits(n-x))) == 0)); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jun 09 2026
